{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ee6525d9-da77-43ab-a55d-b6a8addbcc0f","content":"The issue is classic F# file ordering. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`). F# compiles files in the order they're listed, so `Domain.fs` must come first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_fxSgCRpBz8syaq8Pdj0aZZ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-28345a08a4a94b05bdda9094fe5c8886/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-28345a08a4a94b05bdda9094fe5c8886/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"95871171-e3e4-455e-b3c6-38dd047521d7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed earlier in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, which means it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` is listed after `Services.fs`, the compiler hasn't seen it yet when compiling `Services.fs`.\n\nThe fix is to reorder: `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":462,"requestId":"5C07:1B3F6B:1DA353A:2165974:6A07C84E"},"id":"13d9761f-a276-413b-ac64-49c1e87b1da5","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:28:53.785Z","parentId":"7c0ad766-51a5-4441-928c-1a9e8854972e"}
